/aztea-eval/

# Tool caches (user-local; never committed)
.qwen/
# /cso security reports — narrate the attack surface in plain text; keep local.
.gstack/
# .agents/ is user-local, EXCEPT TODO.md and reference/ — those are team-tracked.
# TODO.md is the source of truth for launch blockers; reference/ holds the deep
# contributor docs that CLAUDE.md (the resolver index) points into. Both are
# referenced from every agent-onboarding doc (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, CODEX.md,
# GEMINI.md). To make the negation work, we cannot wholesale-ignore the
# directory; instead ignore its contents and carve out the tracked paths.
.agents/*
!.agents/TODO.md
!.agents/reference/
!.agents/reference/*.md
.superpowers/
skills/
skills-lock.json
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.hypothesis/
.release-venv/
core/runs.jsonl
docs/personal/
.demo-venv/

# Throwaway dev scripts (Phase-0 spikes, bench expanders, ad-hoc probes).
# Used to answer one-off questions about the codebase; never source of record.
scratch/
